
---
title: "GraphQL Schema Organization"
description: "To be applied to the project implementation of qraphQL API through the gqlgen library"
globs: 
- "gqlgen.yml"
- "graph/**"
- "transport/graphql/**"
alwaysApply: false
version: "1.0.0"
schema: "cursor-mdc-v1"
tags: ["architecture", "go", "graphql", "clean-architecture", "postgresql"]
cursor:
  version: "1.0.0"
  features: ["context-aware generation", "architecture guidance"]
  experimental: false
---

<cursor:rules>
- GraphQL schema should be split by **domain areas**:
  - `graph/schema/flags.graphqls`
  - `graph/schema/experiments.graphqls`
  - `graph/schema/audit.graphqls`
  - `graph/schema/users.graphqls`

- Common types (scalars, enums) can go into `graph/schema/common.graphqls`.

- Use `schema-first` approach with gqlgen:  
  -> run `go run github.com/99designs/gqlgen generate` from project root.  
  -> run `go get [package] if the previous command failed on a missing package or a use of one in a wrong version.  
  -> The config (`gqlgen.yml`) should point to schema and the desired output paths.
</cursor:rules>

### gqlgen Config Example (excerpt)


schema:

graph/schema/common.graphqls

graph/schema/flags.graphqls

graph/schema/experiments.graphqls

exec:
filename: graph/generated.go
package: graph

model:
filename: graph/models_gen.go
package: model

resolver:
layout: follow-schema
dir: transport/graphql
package: graphql
filename_template: "{name}.resolvers.go"
